  .d-flex.flex-column
    .row.mb-3
      .col-lg-6
        .card.mb-4
          .card-body
            h5.card-title Problem description
            p.card-text
              | This term project for my master combines everything I've learned so far about
              | distributed applications and system design. This project implements a backend for a
              | museum. Based on a functional analisys business scenarios are extracted. After an
              | analysis phase the scenarios are converted into a distributed system architecture.
              br
              | The application is developed completely in Java using Quarkus. The containers are
              | deployed in a Kubernetes cluster that runs in the UGent datacenter.

        .card.mb-4
          .card-body
            h5.card-title Business scenarios

            .d-flex.flex-column
              div
                p
                  strong Ticket Sales:
                  |  Users can purchase tickets valid for specific dates. Bulk ticket purchases are
                  | allowed. Capacity depends on the number of guards present.

              div
                p
                  strong Ratings and Recommendations:
                  |  Users can view paintings online and give ratings. Curators use user feedback for
                  | museum management. Users can get personalized recommendations for future visits.

              div
                p
                  strong Artwork Catalog:
                  |  There is a catalog that stores all paintings and exhibits. Paintings are
                  | assigned to spots in the museum and exhibits are planned.

              div
                p
                  strong Staff Management:
                  |  Guard work schedules are maintained. Guards can have fixed or flexible
                  | contracts. Visitor capacity depends on the number of guards. Qualified guides
                  | are allocated for different exhibitions.

      .col-lg-6.d-flex.align-items-stretch
        .card.mb-4
          img.card-img(src="/images/quarkus/Dall-E/museum-hallway3.jpg" alt="Card image cap")

    .mb-1
      h4 Technology
      p
        | The application is developed completely in Java using Quarkus. The containers are
        | deployed in a Kubernetes cluster that runs in the UGent datacenter. Data objects in our
        | application are stored and managed in the MongoDB database using Quarkus Panache.
        | Keycloak is employed as an identity and access management solution to secure and
        | authenticate users in our application. In addition, SmallRye Mutiny was utilized to
        | implement asynchronous and reactive
        | programming.

    .mb-3
      h4 Decomposition
      p
        | The final system architecture splits the business scenarios into five contained microservices that
        | each have their own tasks, privileges and endpoints. The service diagram below shows how the various
        | services interact with each other.

    .row.mb-5
      .col-lg-4.d-flex.align-items-stretch
        .card.mb-4
          .card-body
            h5.card-title Microservices

            ul
              li
                strong Tickets:
                |  Handles ticket and tour orders, with maximum capacity determined by the personnel
                | service.
              li
                strong Personnel:
                |  Manages staff scheduling, including guards and exhibition guides, with a work
                | schedule for each.
              li
                strong Catalog:
                |  Stores paintings and exhibitions. The curator can manage art and exhibition
                | data.
              li
                strong Ratings:
                |  Records visitor ratings for paintings. Ratings can be retrieved by curators.
              li
                strong Analytics:
                |  Generates personalized recommendations for visitors based on their ratings.

      .col-lg-8.d-flex.align-items-stretch
        .card.mb-4
          img.card-img(src="/images/quarkus/systeemontwerp.png" alt="Card image cap")
